WEBVTT

00:01:57.887 --> 00:02:01.355
I'm going to read you a short snippet
from a children's book

00:02:01.379 --> 00:02:04.503
by one of our favorite authors
in the children's room, Eric Carle.

00:02:04.527 --> 00:02:07.544
Some of you might know his work
"The Very Hungry Caterpillar."

00:02:07.568 --> 00:02:11.220
But this is from "'Slowly, Slowly,
Slowly,' said the Sloth."

00:02:13.288 --> 00:02:15.415
"Finally, the sloth replied,

00:02:15.439 --> 00:02:18.500
'It is true that I am slow,
quiet and boring.

00:02:19.177 --> 00:02:20.709
I am lackadaisical,

00:02:20.733 --> 00:02:22.466
I dawdle and I dillydally.

00:02:23.210 --> 00:02:26.456
I am also unflappable, languid, stoic,

00:02:26.480 --> 00:02:29.504
impassive, sluggish, lethargic,

00:02:29.528 --> 00:02:32.641
placid, calm, mellow,